The initial positive test results are still to be confirmed by the NICD but the school has been closed and parents asked to collect their children. Education MEC Kwazi Mshengu has more on the story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A pre-school pupil in Richards Bay, KwaZulu-Natal, has been privately tested COVID-19 and tested positive. The test results are still to be confirmed by the NICD, but the school has been closed and parents asked to collect their children. Some 17 pupils in the child's class have begun showing symptoms of infection. EXPLAINER: How long can coronavirus survive on surfaces KZN Education MEC Kwazi Mshengu said the department was informed by the principal of the school after a private doctor informed the principal. Mshengu said the case was tested by a private lab and had to be verified with the NICD. READ: Test 'every suspected case' of COVID-19: WHO All the learners were screened for the virus and will be tested should the child be positively identified with the virus. Mshengu said it is undoubtedly that the impact of the virus will be extensive but the government is attempting to mitigate the impact of the spread of infection. South Africa has closed the majority of its border posts following an increase in infections in the country. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced control measures for the viral outbreak on Sunday evening. Cabinet Ministers have outlined their plans to deal with the growing Covid-19 pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.